    "body": "right, the way we currently filter is by looking at the compiler output and we're currently not differentiating between dep Test Contract and local contract.\r\n\r\nI'd consider this a bug, even though I'd recommend keeping mock/utils separately from tests.\r\n\r\nFor anyone who wants to pick this up, the ideal fix would be to modify the `Filter`\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/be7084e74247a9880c4357d444143d03fc2269e5/cli/src/cmd/forge/test/filter.rs#L8-L13\r\n\r\nso that it knows what the project's dependency paths are and match them accordingly.\r\n\r\nSo ideally we need some new wrapper type that uses `Filter` and `libs` from the `Config`, then this new type also should implement `TestFilter` with modified `matches_path`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/blob/be7084e74247a9880c4357d444143d03fc2269e5/cli/src/cmd/forge/test/filter.rs#L164",
